createShield(25.10)                                        createShield(25.10)

Name
       createShield - Creates shield wires for the NanoRoute router

Syntax
       createShield

       [-help]

       [-selected]

       [-crosstie_only]

       [-include_fixed]

       Creates  shield  wires  for  the  NanoRoute  router. After creating the
       shields, the router generates a report that includes shielding coverage
       statistics.

Parameters
       -crosstie_only
              Adds crosstie for coaxial shielding only.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information  for each createShield parameter. For a detailed de-
              scription of the command and all of its parameters, use the  man
              command

              man createShield

       -include_fixed
              Includes fixed wires for shielding. The wire will not be changed
              but  the  electrical  characteristics  can  be altered by adding
              shielding so that this option is required to include  the  fixed
              wire for shielding.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -selected
              Creates  shield wires for the selected nets. If you do not spec-
              ify this option, all the clock nets will be shielding.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Example
              * The following command creates shield wires for selected nets:

                createShield -selected

Related Information
              * deleteShield

              * reportShield

              * Using the NanoRoute Router chapter in the Innovus User Guide

                * Performing Shielded Routing

